start.label: it's ill wind that blows nobody any good

examples.en: Laughter was a rare occurrence in his classroom.
Flooding in the area is a common occurrence.
Getting headaches has become a common occurrence for her.
The greatest occurrence of coronary heart disease is in those over 65.
The frequent occurrence of earthquakes in the area means that the buildings must be specifically designed to withstand the force.
They warned that the rain forests are in danger of extinction unless the world's industrial powers concert a plan to prevent such an occurrence.
